# Chhattisgarh

A [State](/States_and_union_territories_of_India) in [Central India](/Central_India), [India](/India), [Chhattisgarh](/Chhattisgarh) exists as a landlocked entity, a geographical quirk nestled in the vastness of the subcontinent. It holds the distinction of being the [ninth largest state by area](/List_of_states_and_union_territories_of_India_by_area), a substantial mass of land that, despite its size, often seems to glide under the radar. With a population that hovers around the 30 million mark, it is simultaneously the [seventeenth most populous](/List_of_states_and_union_territories_of_India_by_population), a balance of space and populace that many more congested regions could only dream of, or perhaps dread.

Its borders, like ancient fault lines, trace paths against seven other [states](/States_and_union_territories_of_India): [Uttar Pradesh](/Uttar_Pradesh) to the north, [Madhya Pradesh](/Madhya_Pradesh) to the northwest, [Maharashtra](/Maharashtra) to the southwest, [Jharkhand](/Jharkhand) to the northeast, [Odisha](/Odisha) to the east, and finally, [Andhra Pradesh](/Andhra_Pradesh) and [Telangana](/Telangana) to the south. This intricate web of connections places Chhattisgarh firmly at the geographical heart of the nation, a silent nexus of diverse cultures and landscapes.

Once an integral, if somewhat overlooked, part of [Madhya Pradesh](/Madhya_Pradesh), Chhattisgarh finally achieved its own distinct [statehood on 1 November 2000](/Chhattisgarh_Rajyotsava). This administrative separation, a relatively recent historical event, saw [Raipur](/Raipur) designated as its capital, a city tasked with anchoring the aspirations of a newly independent region. The state is not just a modern construct, however; its history stretches back millennia, with architectural marvels like the [Bhoramdeo Temple](/Bhoramdeo_Temple) standing testament to its ancient heritage. Its future, at least in planning documents, includes the development of [Nava Raipur](/Naya_Raipur) as a modern, meticulously designed urban center. Natural wonders, like the dramatic [Teerathgarh Falls](/Teerathgarh_Falls) and the majestic [Chitrakote Falls](/Chitrakote_Falls), punctuate its landscape, while cultural touchstones such as the towering [Ghasidas Jaitkham](/Giraudpuri) and the vibrant [Bastar Dussehra](/Bastar_Dussehra) underscore its unique identity. Furthermore, the [Kanger Ghati National Park](/Kanger_Ghati_National_Park) offers a glimpse into the rich biodiversity that thrives within its borders.

Its official identity is encapsulated in the [Emblem of Chhattisgarh](/Emblem_of_Chhattisgarh), a symbol that, like all such emblems, attempts to distill a complex reality into a few stylized strokes.

